The paper deals with the impact of channel aging on the performance of massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of low-cost transceivers, which is a topic related to communication systems (cs.COM). The analysis of the performance of different precoding techniques involves system-level optimization and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the use of large antenna arrays, which is a topic related to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
